        <mxCell id="CIgl6ThwhyX5Au9De2Gi-17" value="&lt;h1 style=&quot;margin-top: 0px;&quot;&gt;Case API&lt;/h1&gt;&lt;div&gt;The backend currently scans the entire &lt;code&gt;cases&lt;/code&gt;, &lt;code&gt;users&lt;/code&gt;, &lt;code&gt;booklets&lt;/code&gt;, &lt;code&gt;bookmarks&lt;/code&gt;, &lt;code&gt;slideshows&lt;/code&gt;, &lt;code&gt;sidecards&lt;/code&gt;, and other tables to compile data into the case summary. This process causes significant delays for admins and client admins when loading results on the Cases page. The issue will worsen as the number of cases increases.&lt;/div&gt;" style="text;html=1;whiteSpace=wrap;overflow=hidden;rounded=0;" parent="1" vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry x="530" y="320" width="350" height="150" as="geometry" />
